### What to Do

Implement golden file testing to ensure JSON output (used by agents) NEVER changes unexpectedly.

### Why Golden Files?

Agent integrations depend on the EXACT structure of dcg's JSON output. Even adding a new field could break parsing. Golden files catch these changes.

### Golden File Structure

```
tests/golden/
├── hook/
│   ├── allow_simple.json       # "echo hello" → allow
│   ├── allow_complex.json      # Complex but safe command
│   ├── deny_filesystem.json    # "rm -rf /" → deny
│   ├── deny_git.json           # "git push --force" → deny
│   ├── deny_kubernetes.json    # "kubectl delete ns prod" → deny
│   └── deny_database.json      # "DROP DATABASE" → deny
├── cli/
│   ├── doctor_healthy.txt      # Normal doctor output
│   ├── doctor_unhealthy.txt    # Doctor with errors
│   ├── packs_list.txt          # Pack listing
│   └── explain_trace.txt       # Explain output
└── stderr/
    ├── denial_critical.txt     # Critical severity denial (stripped ANSI)
    ├── denial_high.txt         # High severity denial
    └── denial_no_color.txt     # NO_COLOR=1 output
```

### Test Implementation

```rust
// tests/golden_tests.rs

use std::path::Path;
use serde_json::Value;

/// Compare JSON output against golden file
fn assert_json_matches_golden(actual: &str, golden_path: &str) {
    let golden_content = std::fs::read_to_string(
        Path::new("tests/golden").join(golden_path)
    ).expect(&format!("Golden file not found: {}", golden_path));

    let actual_json: Value = serde_json::from_str(actual)
        .expect("Actual output is not valid JSON");
    let golden_json: Value = serde_json::from_str(&golden_content)
        .expect("Golden file is not valid JSON");

    // Compare key-by-key for better error messages
    if actual_json != golden_json {
        let diff = json_diff(&golden_json, &actual_json);
        panic!(
            "JSON output differs from golden file '{}':\n{}",
            golden_path, diff
        );
    }
}

#[test]
fn hook_allow_simple_matches_golden() {
    let output = run_hook_mode("echo hello");
    assert_json_matches_golden(&output.stdout, "hook/allow_simple.json");
}

#[test]
fn hook_deny_filesystem_matches_golden() {
    let output = run_hook_mode("rm -rf /");
    assert_json_matches_golden(&output.stdout, "hook/deny_filesystem.json");
}

#[test]
fn hook_deny_git_matches_golden() {
    let output = run_hook_mode("git push --force origin main");
    assert_json_matches_golden(&output.stdout, "hook/deny_git.json");
}
```

### JSON Diff Helper

```rust
fn json_diff(expected: &Value, actual: &Value) -> String {
    let mut diffs = Vec::new();

    fn diff_values(path: &str, exp: &Value, act: &Value, diffs: &mut Vec<String>) {
        match (exp, act) {
            (Value::Object(e), Value::Object(a)) => {
                // Check for missing/extra keys
                for key in e.keys() {
                    if !a.contains_key(key) {
                        diffs.push(format!("MISSING: {}.{}", path, key));
                    }
                }
                for key in a.keys() {
                    if !e.contains_key(key) {
                        diffs.push(format!("EXTRA: {}.{}", path, key));
                    }
                }
                // Recurse on shared keys
                for key in e.keys().filter(|k| a.contains_key(*k)) {
                    diff_values(
                        &format!("{}.{}", path, key),
                        &e[key], &a[key], diffs
                    );
                }
            }
            _ if exp != act => {
                diffs.push(format!(
                    "CHANGED: {} expected {:?} got {:?}",
                    path, exp, act
                ));
            }
            _ => {}
        }
    }

    diff_values("$", expected, actual, &mut diffs);
    diffs.join("\n")
}
```

### Updating Golden Files

When intentionally changing output, update goldens:

```bash
# Update all golden files
UPDATE_GOLDEN=1 cargo test --features rich-output golden

# Or manually regenerate specific file
echo "rm -rf /" | ./target/release/dcg --hook-mode > tests/golden/hook/deny_filesystem.json
```

### CI Protection

```yaml
# .github/workflows/golden.yml
- name: Check golden file stability
  run: cargo test --features rich-output golden

- name: Fail on golden changes
  run: |
    if git diff --exit-code tests/golden/; then
      echo "Golden files unchanged ✓"
    else
      echo "::error::Golden files changed! This may break agent integrations."
      echo "If intentional, update with: UPDATE_GOLDEN=1 cargo test golden"
      exit 1
    fi
```

### Critical Fields That Must Never Change

```json
{
  "verdict": "deny|allow",  // NEVER CHANGE
  "reason": "string",       // NEVER CHANGE
  "pack": "string|null",    // NEVER CHANGE
  "pattern": "string|null"  // NEVER CHANGE
  // New fields can be ADDED but existing ones MUST remain
}
```
